Six suspects have been arrested and R10 million worth of drugs seized at Kempton Park and Edenvale, east of Johannesburg. Police say cocaine, kat, crystal meth and dagga were found during a raid. Gauteng police spokesperson Mavela Masondo says, “Following a multi-disciplinary intelligence driven operation that was consisting of the Hawks, crime intelligence and tracing unit police raided about six houses in Kempton Park and Edenvale. This is where six suspects were arrested – two females and four males. The suspects will be appearing at Kempton Park court on Monday.” 